<HEADLINE>
FEDS SEEK INFORMATION FROM HOMESTORE.COM
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
(Also moving in the ``a'' national news file.) 
By JASON Z. COHEN 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Thousand Oaks, Calif. _ The U.S. Justice Department's Antitrust
Division is investigating the online realty industry for possible
anti-competitive practices and has requested information from
Homestore.com Inc., officials said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   This is the same government entity that is prosecuting Microsoft
Corp.
</P>
<P>
   The Thousand Oaks-based home portal has complied with the
request for information about its business practices and the
dynamics of the industry, Chief Financial Officer John Giesecke
said.
</P>
<P>
   The government sought basic information, he said.
</P>
<P>
   ``We don't believe we've done anything that would violate any
law or regulation,'' Giesecke said.
