   &UR; CAMPAIGN _ (Moved in ``p'' category) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   NRA-REPUBS (Washington) _ The National Rifle Association is
embracing the Republican Party more openly, and firmly, than ever
with huge soft money contributions as well as fund-raising letters
and speeches promoting George W. Bush. By James Dao.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WASHINGTON _ (Moved in ``w'' category)  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ZOO-SHOOTINGS _ The shooting of seven teen-agers on Monday
outside the gates of the National Zoo, one of Washington's top
tourist attractions, has jolted the city's sense of
self-satisfaction that built during the 1990s with a new reformist
mayor, a budget surplus and reduced crime. By Steven A. Holmes.
</P>
<P>
   DRUG-PRICES _ Prices for the 50 drugs most frequently used by
the elderly increased at twice the rate of inflation in the last
year, according to a new study. By Robert Pear.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Graphic has been sent to NYT graphics clients.)
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-U.S.-TRADE _ The White House has scaled back its lobbying
efforts on China trade after warnings that its aggressive campaign
to persuade Congress to pass permanent trade relations violated
legal restrictions on executive branch lobbying. Though there's
been no official finding of wrongdoing, the White House ``war
room'' on China trade has become a low-key operation after a
complaint prompted a GAO investigation. By Joseph Kahn.
</P>
