   (ART ADV: Photos [NYT22,23) have been sent to NYT photo
clients.)
</P>
<P>
   EURO-MARKETPLACE (Undated) _ American investors who decided to
diversify into European stock markets this year have been killed by
the euro, which seems to be on a relentless decline. The major
European stock indexes are up, this year's 8.5 percent decline in
the euro has turned those positives into negatives. By Jonathan
Fuerbringer.
</P>
<P>
   TOBACCO-AD-COLUMN (New York) _ In a bizarre recording that
simultaneously pokes fun at itself and, apparently, at the campaign
to keep children from smoking, Brown &AMP; Williamson Tobacco has been
serenading callers for several months with what may be the worst
jingle in commercial history: Oooh, the tobacco plant is a lovely
plant, / Its leaves so broad and green. / But you shouldn't think
about the tobacco plant / If you're still a teen. By Michael Pollak
</P>
