Kahn's Judaica is on exhibit in La Jolla, Calif. By Susan Kleinman.
</P>
<P>
   TALIBAN-BOOK-REVIEW (Undated) _ In his new book, ``Taliban,''
Ahmed Rashid shows most conspicuously how religion, ethnic
factionalism and outside meddling combined in Afghanistan to
produce a brutal sequel to the anti-Soviet war of the 1980s,
bringing to power in the process the backward-looking, anti-female,
drug-trading, terror-supporting, massacre-inducing Taliban.
Reviewed by Richard Bernstein.
</P>
<P>
   INDIA-FILM-REVIEW (Undated) _ An impoverished Indian village in
the state of Kerala learns of a wonderful U.S. product that will
make life better, bring the people glory and put the village on the
international map: an electric chair, or ``electronic chair,'' as
it's called in Murali Nair's dryly devastating movie ``Throne of
Death.'' Reviewed by Stephen Holden.
</P>
<P>
