<P>
   SRC - t's a different time for the Southern Regional Council,
the long-time think tank for the Civil Rights Movement. Back in the
1960s, the SRC and other civil rights groups were helped by
violent, white Southern males _ like infamous Birmingham police
chief Bull Connor, who turned dogs on black protesters _ who helped
illustrate the plight of minorities. As the SRC celebrates its 80th
anniversary Thursday in Atlanta, president Charles Johnson reflects
on where the group is going and where it's been. (Maunel, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
