not going away. Stone Mountain Mayor Chuck Burris, first black
mayor of the city long associated with the Confederacy, ordered
down a flagpole that the Sons of Confederate Veterans put up to fly
the Rebel flag for Confederate Memorial Day on Wednesday. Now that
group says it will sue. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
