   SCHOOL-CHIEFS WASHINGTON _ New ways of improving teacher quality
are outlined and urged Wednesday by 8 state education chiefs in the
Education Leaders Council, a rival to the long-dominant Council of
Chief State School Officers. From states that educate 30 percent of
the nation's public school kids, the 8 breakaway school chiefs
include those in the Cox states of Colorado, Georgia, Florida and
Texas. (Mollison, Cox News Service)
