<P>
   KELSO-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ I've thought up a way the federal
government could appear a little less heavy-handed the next time it
conducts a raid involving an impressionable young child. My
suggestion would be to dress up all of those menacing federal
agents in kid-friendly mascot suits _ you know, like Sylvester the
Cat, Tweety Bird and Bugs Bunny. ``Eh, what's up, Doc? Spread
'em.'' (Kelso, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED
