   FOOD
</P>
<P>
   SAUCE _ DAYTON, Ohio _ When Dayton Dragons fans buy their first
hot dogs and burgers at Fifth Third Field today, they'll find
something new alongside the ketchup and mustard bottles _ Mrs.
Wrights' Sauce. (Heller, Dayton Daily News) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   SAUCE-SIDE _ A little more about the sauce itself. (Dayton Daily
News) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   HOME-BREW _ This is a tale of a good beer that tested the faith
of two home brewers. We were braced to stand before you utter
failures. We believed we had wasted the time of Pierre Celis, a
gentleman and a brewer whom we admire _ nay, worship. Our batch of
grand cru was invaded by something, and what began as a promising
golden brew looked like a description author James Ellroy used to
describe the sky over Los Angeles: carcinogenic tan. In the
presence of Pierre Celis, we feared we'd brewed the lousiest beer
you ever had. Alas, a good beer will always outlast.
(Lisheron/Beach, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   COXNET FOOD _ (EDS: This is the CoxNet FOOD page for the current
week. This layout is now available.)
