<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TRAVEL-SHOPPING-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SHOPPING AROUND: A WALKING-TOUR SAMPLER  
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
   ATTENTION EDITORS: The following material from The New York Times
Syndicate is for use by WAY TO GO! clients. Nonsubscribers can use
this article only by special arrangement. For purchase information,
see end of text. 
 &HT;    
 (PLEASE NOTE: This article has been transmitted twice _ into the
``t'' travel news and ``l'' lifestyle news files.)  
 &HT;    
 By EVERETT POTTER  
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
 &HT;    ``Slow down to see the world'' is not only the motto of tour
operator Butterfield &AMP; Robinson. It's probably the single best
reason to take a walking trip, whether in Colorado, France or
Turkey.
 &HT;    Here's a selection of walking trips that spans the globe. Prices
are per person, based on double occupancy, and land-only unless
otherwise noted.
 &HT;     Backroads  (801 Cedar St., Berkeley, Calif. 94710;
800-GO-ACTIVE; www.backroads.com) has walks that cover the world.
Among them is a new ``Walking Turkey'' trip. This 10-day adventure,
with departures in May, June, September and October, begins in
Cappadocia. After several days of walking, guests fly to the coast
and spend four days on yachts, kayaking and snorkeling through a
sunken Lycian city. The cost is $3,998.
 &HT;     Butterfield &AMP; Robinson  (70 Bond St., Toronto, Ontario, Canada,
M5B 1X3; 800-678-1147; www.butterfield.com) has many walking trips
for travelers inclined to high-end comforts. Their ``Burgundy:
Classic Walking'' is a signature trip, featuring six days of wine
tasting and walking through France's most prestigious wine-growing
area. Accommodations include Chateau de Bagnols, one of the
region's finest hotels. Departures are in May, June, August and
September, and the cost is $3,925.
 &HT;     Canadian Mountain Holidays  (Box 1660, Banff, Alberta, Canada;
800-661-0252; www.cmhhike.com) is perhaps the best known
heli-hiking company in North America. Each day of these lodge-based
trips begins with a helicopter ride up to about 8,200 feet. Guests
hike all day and then get picked up by the helicopter and return to
the lodge. A classic three-night heli-hiking trip, staying at
either Bobbie Burns Lodge or Bugaboo Lodge in the Canadian Rockies,
starts at $1,280 (Canadian), about $882 (U.S.). There are
departures from June through September.
 &HT;     Ciclismo Classico  (30 Marathon St., Arlington, Mass. 02474;
800-866-7314; www.ciclismoclassico.com) has a number of new trips,
including ``Sicily's Ancient Pathways.'' This eight-day adventure
offers a rigorous hike up the active volcanoes Etna and Stromboli,
as well as an exploration of Taormina and Ragusa. There are
departures in October, and the cost is $2,395.
 &HT;     Country Walkers  (P.O. Box 180, Waterbury, Vt. 05676;
800-464-9255; www.countrywalkers.com) has a variety of trips,
including ``New Mexico: Santa Fe and Taos.'' This six-day trip
gives walkers a chance to see Georgia O'Keefe's Ghost Ranch, Taos
Pueblo and cliff dwellings at Bandelier National Monument. The
price is $1,995, and there are departures in May, June, September
and October.
 &HT;     La Dolce Via  (6420 Fairmount Ave., El Cerrito, Calif. 94530;
877-77DOLCE; www.ladolcevia.com) is the new luxury
biking-and-walking division of Mountain Travel Sobek. On these
trips, culture and comfort reign. ``Heart of Umbria'' is a 10-day
trip to the so-called ``green heart'' of Italy, with a chance to
see such towns as Amelia, Assisi and Gubbio. There are departures
in May, June and September, and the price is $2,890.
 &HT;     Maupintrek  (1421 Research park Drive, Suite 300, Lawrence,
Kan. 66049; 800-255-4266; www.maupintour.com) is the
adventure-travel division of Maupintour. They have a variety of
trips around the world, including the ``Gaelic Hiking Expedition.''
This nine-day walk and trek goes to County Donegal, Glenveagh
National Park and Tory Island, one of the most remote spots in the
country. The trip concludes with several days in Wicklow. The cost
is $2,430, and there are departures from July through September.
 &HT;     New England Hiking Holidays  (P.O. Box 1648, North Conway, N.H.
03860; 800-869-0949; www.nehikingholidays.com) has walks throughout
North America and Europe as well as in their own back yard.
``Vermont: Northeast Kingdom'' is a chance to spend five days
exploring the most remote corner of the state. That includes seeing
the glacial Lake Willoughby and staying at country inns, including
the Trapp Family Lodge in Stowe. Departures are in May and from
July through October. The price starts at $1,195.
 &HT;     REI Adventures  (P.O. Box 1938, Sumner, Wash. 98390;
800-622-2236; www.rei.com/travel) offers a new trip for hikers
called ``Colorado Trails.'' This seven-day journey begins in
Crested Butte. Later on, hikers sleep in cabins at 11,500 feet and
hike up a 13,000-foot peak. The price is $1,195 plus $15 for a
lifetime membership in REI. There are departures from July through
September.
 &HT;     Thomson Safaris  (347 Broadway, Cambridge, Mass. 02139;
800-235-0289; www.thomsonsafaris.com) has a new ``Tanzania Walking
and Wildlife Safari'' that explores Tarangire National Park,
Ngorongoro Crater and Serengetti National Park. This 17-day
adventure is $5,990, with departures from June to October. The
price includes international airfare from either Boston or New
York.
 &HT;     The Wayfarers  (172 Bellevue Ave., Newport, R.I. 02840;
800-249-4620; www.thewayfarers.com) may be best known for English
walking trips, but they also cover the continent with style. ``The
Gourmet Provence'' is a seven-day trip that combines easy walking
with cooking classes. Walkers get to visit such Provencal villages
as Lacoste and visit the market at Cavaillon with chef Jean Jacques
Prevot. The cost is $3,440, and there are departures in June and
October.
 &HT;     Whole Journeys  (1500 E. 128th Ave., Thornton, Colo. 80241;
877-745-4648; www.wholejourneys.com) has trips to a relatively
undiscovered region of Italy. ``Sabina: Grape Harvest'' is an
eight-day walk through an area not far from Rome. Accommodations
are at three-star ``agritourismo'' apartments. The departure is in
October, and the cost is $2,295.
 &HT;    -----
 &HT;    (Everett Potter is a New York City-based free-lance travel
writer.) 
 &HT;    -----
 c.2000 Everett Potter 
<TEXT>
 &UR; EDITOR: Visit The New York Times Syndicate Web site at
http://www.nytimes.com/syndicate for more information on The WAY TO
GO! travel package and other features. &QL;
