   &UR; OTHER NATIONAL GENERAL &LR;  (``a'' code)
</P>
<P>
   PASSOVER-RESORTS (Ft. Lauderdale, Fla.) _ They're a far cry and
a long way from the Catskills. Luxury resorts around the world a
now catering to the Passover trade and going to remarkable lengths
to make things kosher. By Laurie Goodstein.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   JANITORS-UNREST (Chicago) _ Some 3,500 janitors here are the
latest to walk the picket line. Union leaders are trying to make
them the leading spokesmen for the poor to address a shameful
income gap in a time of prosperity. Elsewhere, janitors are on
strike in San Diego and contracts in Oakland, Calif., Cleveland and
Seattle will expire within the next few months. By Steve
Greenhouse.
