<P>
   CAMPAIGN-BRIEFS (Undated) _ News and notes from the campaign.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SCIENCE &LR;  (``a'' code)
</P>
<P>
   SCI-COSMOLOGY (Undated) _ NASA announced Wednesday of the most
detailed study yet of the cosmic microwave background radiation,
widely believed to be the remnant of the big bang fireball that
began the universe. The results have left cosmologists both elated
and puzzled. As reported last November the data show that the
geometry of the universe on large scales is Euclidean _ or ``flat''
in physics jargon _ confirming a general view favored by theorists.
However further analysis of the data show that the universe seems
to lack a feature that is predicted by those same favored theories,
suggesting that cosmologists do not understand the workings of the
big bang as well as they thought they did. By James Glanz. (1000
words) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; CIRCUITS &LR;  (``a'' code)
