<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-26 14:43 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A7719 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r d BC-RECIPES-BUNDY-TEX     04-26 0579
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-RECIPES-BUNDY-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PERKED-UP PICKLES, FRENCH DRESSING AND APPLE PIE A LA JERRY'S
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BEVERLY BUNDY 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   James Goreham sent in a recipe for a French salad dressing. He
doesn't know if it's the one Brenda Canning of Granbury requested,
but he recommends it nonetheless.
</P>
<P>
   Ada Mortenson's request for lime-treated pickles brought many
responses. Pickling lime can be found in the canning supply section
of the supermarket.
</P>
<P>
   And finally, we had a request to rerun the recipe for the apple
pie that was served at Jerry's Drive-In in Fort Worth.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   FRENCH DRESSING
</P>
<P>
   Yields 4 cups
</P>
<P>
   10-ounce can tomato soup
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 cups vegetable oil
</P>
<P>
   3/4 cup apple cider vinegar
</P>
<P>
   1 cup sugar
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon pepper
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon salt
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon prepared mustard (optional)
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon onion, ground
</P>
<P>
   Garlic salt to taste
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Mix on low speed for 10 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per tablespoon: 62 calories, 5 grams fat, 4
grams carbohydrates, trace protein, 0 cholesterol, 144 milligrams
sodium, 76 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   LIME PICKLES
</P>
<P>
   Yields 8 quarts
</P>
<P>
   7 pounds unwaxed cucumbers, sliced
</P>
<P>
   2 cups pickling lime
</P>
<P>
   2 gallons water
</P>
<P>
   Syrup:
</P>
<P>
   8 cups vinegar
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon celery seed
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon salt
</P>
<P>
   9 cups sugar
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon whole cloves
</P>
<P>
   Soak cucumber slices in lime water. Drain and wash thoroughly.
Rinse at least 3 times until water is clear, because lime is
poisonous. Soak 3 hours in clear water. Pour off water, pour syrup
on pickles and let set overnight.
</P>
<P>
   In morning, cook pickles and syrup until pickles look clear,
about 35 minutes. Pack into clean canning jars and seal.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis for 1/4 cup: 41 calories, 0 fat, 11 grams
carbohydrates, trace protein, 0 cholesterol, 19 milligrams sodium.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   JERRY'S DRIVE-IN'S FRENCH APPLE PIE
</P>
<P>
   Serves 8
</P>
<P>
   2 unbaked pie crusts
</P>
<P>
   18- to 20-ounce can apples packed in water
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon lemon juice
</P>
<P>
   2/3 cup sugar
</P>
<P>
   1/3 cup flour
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon cinnamon
</P>
<P>
   4 or 5 thin pats of butter
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon butter
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon vanilla
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon heavy cream
</P>
<P>
   Approximately 1/3 to 1/2 cup powdered sugar
</P>
<P>
   8 pecan halves
</P>
<P>
   Place one pie shell in 9-inch pie plate. Pour apples and their
juice into the shell. Sprinkle with the lemon juice.
</P>
<P>
   Combine sugar, flour and cinnamon, and distribute evenly over
apples. Place butter pats randomly over apple filling. Top with
second pie crust. Bake in 350-degree oven for about 45 minutes, or
until pie is golden.
</P>
<P>
   About 5 or 10 minutes before pie is done, melt 1 tablespoon
butter. Off the heat, whisk in vanilla and heavy cream and sift in
the powdered sugar until mixture reaches thickness of cream gravy.
As soon as pie is removed from oven, slather with the sugar icing.
Mark off 8 servings with the pecan halves.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 431 calories, 21 grams fat, 58
grams carbohydrates, 12 milligrams cholesterol, 270 milligrams
sodium, 44 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   (Beverly Bundy is food editor for the Fort Worth Star-Telegram.
Send recipes and requests to Beverly Bundy, Fort Worth
Star-Telegram, Box 1870, Fort Worth, Texas 76101. Or E-mail to
bbundy(at)star-telegram.com. Include a daytime phone number.
Responses to requests will be made only through this column. Visit
the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
