</P>
<P>
   &UR; THREE MINUTES THAT SHOOK AMERICA _ AND GORE'S CHANCES &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; THREE-MINUTES-ELIAN-INDEPENDENT &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ The high drama of Saturday's pre-dawn raid on the
Miami house of Lazaro Gonzalez lasted a bare three minutes. But the
political and diplomatic reverberations of what happened are likely
to be felt for decades, and many lives have been changed, probably
forever...By Mary Dejevsky, The Independent &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (ATTN: Commentary Editors) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (775 words) &QL;   &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; THE FATE OF SIX-YEAR-OLD HAS THE POWER TO MOVE NATIONS &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ELIAN-EDITORIAL-INDEPENDENT &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (UNDATED) _ It was the picture that went around the world which
will be remembered long after most people have forgotten what the
dispute over Elian Gonzalez was about. But if Elian's
all-too-eventful life could contribute to the ending of America's
counterproductive isolation of Cuba, the shock he endured at five
o'clock Saturday morning may have heralded a larger
accomplishment...By The Editorial Board of The Independent &QL;
