<P>
   &UR; NETANYAHU'S POPULARITY GROWING IN ISRAELI POLLS &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; `BIBI'-REBOUNDS-INDEPENDENT &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   JERUSALEM _ It was James Carville, the gritty Cajun genius
behind Bill Clinton's campaign war room, who came up with the
slogan which turned Ehud Barak from old soldier into Israel's new
prime minister. ``Stuck. Stuck. Stuck,'' it said, indicting
beleaguered Benjamin Netanyahu's performance on almost every front.
Nearly a year later, though, the same staccato mantra could now be
used against the man for whom it helped secure a rare landslide
victory. The wave of giddy optimism that flooded Israel with
Barak's election last May has melted away. And _ against all odds _
Netanyahu is beginning once again to make a serious showing in the
polls...By Phil Reeves, The Independent &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (ATTN: Commentary Editors) &QL;
</P>
