For one thing, he is a benefits attorney and 401(k) plan record
keeper. But when he settles down in front of one of his computers,
Hamilton becomes a dangerous threat to the established order. His
scheme? To turn the 401(k) from a retirement plan dependent on
costly retail mutual funds into one that relies on low-cost
wholesale pension management...By Scott Burns, Worth Magazine &QL;
