<P>
   MICROSOFT-SPLIT (Undated) _ In preparing to ask a federal judge
to approve a breakup of Microsoft, the government is choosing a
course for which there is little precedent as a court-ordered
antitrust remedy. Such an extreme solution has been applied in only
a few cases, and even then in circumstances that _ as Microsoft
will certainly point out _ differ significantly from those of the
software industry. But even if a breakup is a long shot, a century
of antitrust case law shows that a judge has considerable
discretion. By Steve Lohr.
</P>
