<P>
   JONESES _ ATLANTA _ For nearly four decades, there has been a
member of the Jones family either playing or coaching the Albany
State University basketball team. Oliver Jones arrived in south
Georgia from McGehee, Ark. in 1961 and five of his younger brothers
(Melvin, Wilbert, Caldwell, Major and Charles) also played at
Albany State before moving into professional basketball. Oliver has
been head coach at Albany State since 1972, and is the one of the
winningest coach in school history. But after 24 losses last
season, Jones has been forced out as coach. Next season will be the
first in 40 years that one of the Jones brothers has not been
associated with the Albany State program. (Reese, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) 40. WITH PHOTOS.
