</P>
<P>
   APPRECIATE-MERRICK (Undated) _ David Merrick, the colorful and
frequently contentious theater showman, was arguably Broadway's
most successful producer. In the late 1950s and 1960s, he is said
to have grossed $20 million annually. By Maureen Dezell. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   RAYTHEON-MEETING (Boston) _ Shareholders deliver a partial vote
of no confidence to Raytheon Co. at its annual meeting, passing
nonbinding resolutions to reduce antitakeover provisions and to
elect directors more frequently. By Ross Kerber. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   AMGEN-PATENT (Boston) _ Amgen Inc. shares rise nearly five
points, Transkaryotic Therapies Inc. declines more than five points
after a federal judge rules that TKT violated an Amgen patent for
Epogen, the biggest-selling biotech drug. By Ronald Rosenberg. 600
words.
</P>
<P>
   PORSCHE-GIFTS (Undated) _ Computer company plans to reward 22
workers who helped the company double its stock price last year.
They'll receive new Porsches, says Mercury Computer Systems, which
makes embedded computer systems for radar, sonar and other defense
equipment. By Diane E. Lewis. 600 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS (s) &LR;
