<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Thursday, April 27, and thereafter. The stories will carry the
``f'' financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For
questions about stories, please contact Michael McGarr at the the
Daily News at (818) 713-3470.
</P>
<P>
   ENFORMA-SETTLEMENT (Los Angeles) _ In the largest settlement of
its kind, an Encino company that markets a weight-loss system
claiming to block fat and burn calories without exercise agreed
Wednesday to repay $10 million to customers to settle government
chagres that they used deceptive advertising. Enforma Natural
Products, which advertises and sells ``The Enforma System,'' used
infomercials featuring former Dodger star Steve Garvey to pitch the
product. By Chris Sieroty.
</P>
<P>
   AMGEN-RULING (Thousand Oaks, Calif.) _ Amgen Inc. shares jumped
5.4 percent on Wednesday after a federal judge ruled that two
companies infringed on its patent for Epogen, which is used to
treat anemia. The ruling is procedural and does not settle the
dispute between the two companies, but it does make it tougher for
competitor Transkaryotic Therapies Inc. to prevail. By Jason Z.
Cohen.
</P>
