<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SHOPPING-GUIDE27-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Locate hard to find itemsBy Marylin Johnson
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Having trouble finding a particular item? We'll try to help you
locate it. But because of the volume of mail, we cannot track down
every request. Readers whose queries are answered in the column
will receive a blue-and-cream canvas Buyer's Edge tote bag. Write
us at Buyer's Edge Find It,The Atlanta Journal-Constitution, P.O.
Box 4689, Atlanta, GA 30302; e-mail us at buyersedge(at)ajc.com
(please include your name, the city you live in and daytime phone
number); or call 404-582-7642.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I would like to find No Bugs M'Lady paper for my cabinets. I
have used it for years, but now I can't find it.
</P>
<P>
   _Joan Miller, Smyrna, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: All nasty little critters will soon steer clear of your
cabinets. This odorless insecticidal shelf and drawer covering,
which is FDA approved and comes in 20 patterns, kills roaches, ants
and silverfish. You can also put this product in storage areas and
around garbage cans, under sinks and in broom closets. Order No
Bugs M'Lady from Kittrich Corp. A case of 12 18-inch-by-10-foot
rolls is $15.35. 1-800-321-1741.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I am in search of bluejeans by HIS. For years, I bought them
from Target but can't seem to find them anymore. These jeans are
long-lasting and fit well.
</P>
<P>
   _ Bill Bradford, Conyers, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: Your search is over for these easy-care blue denims. Thony's,
111 Peachtree St. S.W. (404-525-0711) carries HIS in waist sizes
30-42. A pair is $29.95.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I find Albert Einstein's No More Smelly Shoes? My
wife complained about my smelly tennis shoes, but after using this
product, I heard no more complaints. But I've lost track of it.
Help me!
</P>
<P>
   _Jerry Blum, Atlanta
</P>
<P>
   A: Only a genius could discover ``No More Smelly Shoes.'' We
located it at the Bed, Bath &AMP; Beyond store at 800 Ernest Barrett
Parkway, Kennesaw (770-499-8863). A bottle is $7.99. Made in
Australia by Dynamo House, this product _ so named ``because it's
such a brilliant idea,'' says the manufacturer _ contains only
natural substances. ``It's nontoxic,'' says a Dynamo House
spokeswoman, ``and its odor-counteracting ability has been
scientifically proven.'' It's simple to use. After wearing, spray
one or two squirts into each shoe. Leave overnight or wear
immediately.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I am trying to locate a toothbrush for people who wear
braces. It's by Butler G.U.M.
</P>
<P>
   _Marilyn Davis, College Park, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: Your dentist will love you. Butler G.U.M.'s version is the
Proxabrush Handle ($2.19). It cleans and removes plaque on
hard-to-reach tooth surfaces and comes with two interdental brush
refills. And Oral-B makes the Interdental Kit ($2.69) which comes
with a handle and two brush refills. It ``effectively cleans around
bridges and braces,'' says the manufacturer. We found both brushes
at CVS, 4860 Stone Mountain Highway, Lilburn (770-972-3057).
</P>
<P>
   Q: I am looking for a card holder so a one-armed person can take
part in a card game. It sits on the table and holds 13 cards.
</P>
<P>
   _Lillian Brown, Atlanta
</P>
<P>
   A: This is your lucky day. We found a Wood Card Holder from
Games of Tradition ($11.95) at the Game Keeper in Phipps Plaza,
3500 Peachtree Road N.E. (404-266-9600). It sits on the table and
holds your playing cards so you don't have to.
</P>
<P>
   NOTE TO READERS:
</P>
<P>
   Several readers have not been able to find Domino Dots, the
sugar cubes. A spokeswoman for Domino Sugar Co. says the New York
plant that makes the cubes has been on strike since June. However,
she's hopeful the strike will be settled in a few weeks and the
plant can again produce the cubes. Watch for them to start
returning to grocery stores in the next few months.
</P>
<P>
   _Contributing: Michelle C. Brooks
</P>
<P>
   Marylin Johnson writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
